t committing another crime, and were denied early release. However, when evaluated a year later, a RAT tool determines you no longer pose a significant threat and are released from prison early on parole.'),(824,48,'_description_for_pop-up_1','field_62b570331175e'),(825,48,'subtitle_1','RAT: discretionary release/parole'),(826,48,'_subtitle_1','field_62b570927557b'),(827,48,'more_info_for_pop-up_1','When deciding whether to release an incarcerated person early on parole (also known as discretionary release), parole boards will consult RATs to determine the individualâ€™s risk of recidivism. This decision is based on factors such as crime severity, length of incarceration, behavior while incarcerated, criminal history, and mental health. Other factors such as education, gender, and age are also taken into account. At this stage, RATs are intended to anticipate an individual reoffending, particularly in a violent way, and are sometimes customized for specific groups (for example, targeting recidivism risk for sex offenders).'),(828,48,'_more_info_for_pop-up_1','field_62b5709e7557c'),(829,48,'title_for_pop-up_2',''),(830,48,'_title_for_pop-up_2','field_62b570281175c'),(831,48,'description_for_pop-up_2',''),(832,48,'_description_for_pop-up_2','field_62b5706211761'),(833,48,'subtitle_2',''),(834,48,'_subtitle_2','field_62b57eb4e3371'),(835,48,'more_info_for_pop-up_2',''),(836,48,'_more_info_for_pop-up_2','field_62b570b77557d'),(837,48,'title_for_pop-up_3',''),(838,48,'_title_for_pop-up_3','field_62b5702b1175d'),(839,48,'description_for_pop-up_3',''),(840,48,'_description_for_pop-up_3','field_62b5706511762'),(841,48,'subtitle_3',''),(842,48,'_subtitle_3','field_62b57eb6e3372'),(843,48,'more_info_for_pop-up_3',''),(844,48,'_more_info_for_pop-up_3','field_62b570c37557e'),(845,48,'lilst_items_item_1',''),(846,48,'_lilst_items_item_1','field_62b570ea75580'),(847,48,'lilst_items_item_2',''),(848,48,'_lilst_items_item_2','field_62b570f575581'),(849,48,'lilst_items_item_3',''),(